snippet.title: Best tablets
snippet.description: CNET editors round up their favorite tablets, including products from Apple, Samsung, and Google.

snippet.title: The story behind $255 billion in gold
snippet.description: Road Trip 2010: It may not get as much attention as the famous Kentucky depository, but the Federal Reserve of New York's collection of gold bars is the largest on the planet.

snippet.title: Samsung Galaxy S5 in gold exclusive to Vodafone
snippet.description: Vodafone is the only network that will carry the Samsung Galaxy S5 in gold when the new Android powerhouse launches on 11 April.

snippet.title: Origin PC EON17-SLX
snippet.description: Cramming the most high-end parts into a massive 17-inch body will top $4,000, but you also get a powerful laptop that has more next-gen gaming muscle than any living-room console.

snippet.title: iPad Mini
snippet.description: If you want the full, polished Apple tablet experience in a smaller package, the iPad Mini is worth the premium price. Otherwise, good alternatives are available for less money.

snippet.title: Bid on a solid-gold Flappy Bird while you still can
snippet.description: You don't need a 14-karat gold Flappy Bird figurine, but you might want to own the cute little thing anyway.

snippet.title: Samsung Galaxy Stellar (Verizon Wireless)
snippet.description: A pretty solid entry-level Android 4.0 handset on its own, the Samsung Galaxy Stellar gets a huge bump in value from the $0 price tag.

snippet.title: Here comes a gold Lightning cable for your gold iPhone 5S
snippet.description: The Midas touch comes to the humble cable: A new Kickstarter project called Juicies+ aims to sell gold-tinted Lightning cables at $18 a piece.

snippet.title: Samsung Galaxy Note 8 (AT&T)
snippet.description: The AT&T version of the Samsung Galaxy Note 8 is a quality tablet, but the Nexus 7 offers contract-free 4G LTE support with better performance at a much better price.

snippet.title: Gold iPhone 5s sells for US$10k on eBay
